commit.message: Remove unused import
Finish removing Landscape badge
Remove a few more unneeded compat clauses
Restore assertion mistakenly removed in d12e85f

Flush output after each line

I've gone back and forth on this one. On the one hand, doing this could
negatively honcho's throughput. On the other, this is the behaviour that
I believe most people expect from honcho, even when piping output to a
file or in other situations where STDOUT is not a TTY.

On balance, I'd rather have the default behaviour be unsurprising, and
so this makes honcho's output line-buffered, regardless of Python's
output buffering settings.
Remove broken Landscape badge
Don't maintain a list of Python versions in a fourth place

Fix coverage reporting

`coverage combine` is not needed and will bail if there isn't actually
anything to combine, which is going to be the case most of the time.

Remove most of honcho.compat

The vast majority was for Python 2/3 compatibility, and is no longer
necessary.

Test on Python 3 only

Also bring tox.ini, setup.py, and Travis config in sync.

Allow `-` (dash) in process type

The de facto Procfile standard allows this.

Closes #206.
Remove unsupported Python 2.6

Also switch lint and docs to Python 3.8.

Use upstart's native logging features (#181)

Removes from the upstart export template the custom log location in favor of using upstart's built-in logging collection, compression, and rotation features. Addresses issue #180.
